NNN

This rule is for version files only, there is no rule definition for baseBlob or snapshot files, see below code.

Also MS says "Changing a blob's tier doesn't affect its last modified time.", so we can have a version file for 31 days old, and rehydrated 6 days ago, this file will not be archived.

https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/storage/blobs/archive-rehydrate-overview

